cs.MA, cs.GT, cs.SY, cs.DS, cs.LG 

The paper deals with the existence and construction of optimal schedulers for continuous-time Markov decision processes (CTMDPs) and Markov games. This involves the study of optimal control and approximation techniques, which are typically studied in the sub-categories of Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA), Game Theory (cs.GT), Control Systems (cs.SY), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), and Machine Learning (cs.LG). Therefore, these are the most likely sub-categories for this paper.
